  "articleSummary": "This article is a step-by-step tutorial on configuring a firewall for a Docker host running Debian/Ubuntu Server. Its core argument is that administrators should use UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) to restrict incoming and outbound traffic, explicitly allowing only necessary services (SSH, HTTP/HTTPS, and Docker’s internal bridge network) while denying everything else by default. The guide provides concrete shell commands for installation, rule setup, enabling the firewall, and validating configuration with `nmap`. The intended audience is Docker host administrators seeking a practical, command-line approach to host-level security.",
